RabbitMQ doesn't auto-propagate W3C `traceparent`/`tracestate` headers like HTTP does. You need to manually inject context into message headers on publish and extract it on consume.

**Service A – Publisher (inject):**

```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;

// Create an ActivitySource for your app
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceA.Messaging");

// When publishing:
using var activity = Source.StartActivity("OrderEvent Send", ActivityKind.Producer);

var props = channel.CreateBasicProperties();
props.Headers ??= new Dictionary<string, object>();

// Inject current trace context into message headers
if (activity?.Context is ActivityContext ctx)
{
    props.Headers["traceparent"] = ctx.ToString();          // "00-traceId-spanId-flags"
    if (activity.TraceStateString is string ts)
        props.Headers["tracestate"] = ts;
}

channel.BasicPublish(exchange, routingKey, props, body);
```

**Service B – Consumer (extract + link):**

```csharp
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceB.Messaging");

// In your consumer callback:
var headers = ea.BasicProperties.Headers;

ActivityContext parentCtx = default;
if (headers?.TryGetValue("traceparent", out var raw) == true)
{
    var traceparent = Encoding.UTF8.GetString((byte[])raw);
    ActivityContext.TryParse(traceparent, null, out parentCtx);
}

// Start a new activity linked to the producer's context
using var activity = Source.StartActivity(
    "OrderEvent Receive",
    ActivityKind.Consumer,
    parentContext: parentCtx   // ← this stitches the trace together
);
```

**Wire up OpenTelemetry in both `Program.cs`:**

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(t => t
        .AddSource("ServiceA.Messaging")   // or "ServiceB.Messaging"
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddOtlpExporter());
```

**Key points:**

- `ActivityContext.ToString()` produces the W3C `traceparent` format — no manual formatting needed.
- RabbitMQ headers store values as `byte[]`, so decode with `Encoding.UTF8.GetString` on the consumer side.
- Passing `parentContext` to `StartActivity` makes the consumer span a **child** of the producer span, giving you one contiguous trace in Jaeger/Zipkin/etc.
- If you prefer a **link** instead of parent-child (common for async messaging), use the `links` parameter instead:
  ```csharp
  var link = new ActivityLink(parentCtx);
  Source.StartActivity("OrderEvent Receive", ActivityKind.Consumer,
      links: new[] { link });
  ```
